//  @(#) TSMC 0.18UM CALIBRE LVS/RC COMMAND FILE 
//  @(#) FOR TSMC 0.18 UM CMOS MIXED SIGNAL GENERAL PURPOSE II 1P6M SALICIDE 1.8V/3.3V SPICE MODELS 
//  @(#) SPICE MODEL DOCUMENT: T-018-CM-SP-007 V1.3 
//  @(#) COMMAND FILE DOCUMENT: T-018-CM-SP-007-C1 
//  @(#) COMMAND FILE VERSION: 1.3a 
//  @(#) COMMAND FILE DATE: 11/28/2016 
//
//  TSMC has developed this deck using Mentor Graphics proprietary SVRF and TVF formats. 
//  The deck is to be used only in Calibre tools.  
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// 

//  Sheet Resistance table for 018 process
    VARIABLE    RVWO    440              //  NW resistor within OD 
    VARIABLE    RVWR    927              //  NW resistor under STI 
    VARIABLE    RVPR    321.8            //  P+Poly resistor w/o Silicide 
    VARIABLE    RVNR    295.3            //  N+Poly resistor w/o Silicide 
    VARIABLE    RVPD    140.6            //  P+Diff resistor w/o Silicide 
    VARIABLE    RVND    61.6             //  N+Diff resistor w/o Silicide 
    VARIABLE    RVPSS   7.90             //  P+Poly resistor w/i Silicide (Width<2um) 
    VARIABLE    RVPSL   7.90             //  P+Poly resistor w/i Silicide (Width>=2um) 
    VARIABLE    RVNSS   7.89             //  N+Poly resistor w/i Silicide (Width<2um) 
    VARIABLE    RVNSL   7.89             //  N+Poly resistor w/i Silicide (Width>=2um) 
    VARIABLE    RVPIS   7.76             //  P+Diff resistor w/i Silicide (Width<2um) 
    VARIABLE    RVPIL   7.76             //  P+Diff resistor w/i Silicide (Width>=2um) 
    VARIABLE    RVNIS   6.82             //  N+Diff resistor w/i Silicide (Width<2um) 
    VARIABLE    RVNIL   6.82             //  N+Diff resistor w/i Silicide (Width>=2um) 
    VARIABLE    RVLR    1037             //  High resistance poly resistor
    VARIABLE    RVM1    0.078            //  Metal-1  resistor 
    VARIABLE    RVM2    0.078            //  Metal-2  resistor 
    VARIABLE    RVM3    0.078            //  Metal-3  resistor 
    VARIABLE    RVM4    0.078            //  Metal-4  resistor 
    VARIABLE    RVM5    0.078            //  Metal-5  resistor 
    VARIABLE    RV8k    0.036            //  8k  Top Metal resistor 
    VARIABLE    RV20k   0.0178           //  20k Top Metal resistor 
    VARIABLE    RV30k   0.00897          //  30k top Metal resistor 
    VARIABLE    RV33k   0.0054           //  33k top Metal Cu resistor 
    VARIABLE    RV40k   0.007            //  40k top Metal resistor 
    VARIABLE    MIMCAP_CA      1.025E-15        //  MIMCAP area capacitance 
    VARIABLE    MIMCAP_CF      2.425E-16        //  MIMCAP fringe capacitance 
    VARIABLE    MIMCAP_1P5_CA  1.475E-15        //  MIMCAP_1P5 area capacitance 
    VARIABLE    MIMCAP_1P5_CF  1.545E-16        //  MIMCAP_1P5 fringe capacitance
    VARIABLE    MIMCAP_2P0_CA  1.955E-15        //  MIMCAP_2P0 area capacitance
    VARIABLE    MIMCAP_2P0_CF  2.700E-16        //  MIMCAP_2P0 fringe capacitance
//  END VARIABLE SETTING

//***********************************************************************************
//***!!! NOTICE !!!***
//***********************************************************************************
//    This LVS file, named as "LVS sheet resistance file", only contains the 
// sheet resistance table which is corresponding to the sheet resistance value
// specified in the spice model document. Please be aware of that this lvs file
// can't be ran alone, otherwise you will get a syntax error message! 
//    Another LVS rule file which is called the "LVS main deck" contains all
// the LVS devices extraction, circuit comparsion and connectivity extraction
// coding and also need the "LVS sheet restance file" for sheet resistance
// reference.
//    To obtain a complete LVS deck, you need to finish the following procedures.
//
// Procedures:
//
// 1. Please download the most update "LVS main deck" from TSMC-online system.
//    Currently, the "LVS main deck" is packed together with the "LVS sheet 
//    resistance file" in TSMC 0.18um Mixed Signal SALICIDE (1.8V/5V) with GPII-A
//    process (Doc. T-018-CM-SP-012-C1). This LVS main deck support all devices
//    from 0.18um LO/MM/MMRF/FLASH/CIS/HV/BCD processes.
//
// 2. Starting to unpack the compressed file (from step 1) and move this LVS
//    sheet resistance file to folder RES_TALBE 
//
// 3. Execute the LVS install program LVS_install.pl (from unpacked directory)
//    and choose the SPICE model and metalization option of your chip step by
//    step, as the result, LVS files will be generated in MAIN_DECK folder
//
//    SPECIAL NOTICE:
//
//      1. Though the "LVS main deck" contains all the devices for TSMC 0.18 um
//         processes, it dosen't mean that you can use all the deivces in your design.
//         For what kind of devices that can be used, please refered to the Spice
//         Model Card corresponded to your process.
//
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//                          CHANGE HISTORY
// 
//    Date      version    who                         Description 
// ---------- ---------- ------- ----------------------------------------------------------
// 09/03/2007    1.0a  Karena Lin    1) Based on BSIM 4.5 spice model, generate    
//                                      1p3m-1p6m Calibre LVS command files. ;  
//  
// 10/01/2008    1.1a  Hank Lii      1) Added mismatch models for 1.8V BJTs  
//                                   2) Revise BJT definition to exclude dnw diode  
//                                   3) Prevent formation of OD and poly resistors due to OD and poly fill 
// 
// 12/22/2008    1.1b  Hank Lii      1) Remove DNW restriction from p+/nw and n+/pw diodes 
//                                   2) Remove DNW restriction from MVT NMOS 
// 
// 01/13/2009    1.1c  Hank Lii      1) Add Missing ERC softchecks for CCI deck 
// 
// 04/20/2010    1.1d  Ares Yen  	 1) Add VDDM in POWER_NAME and add VSSM in GROUND_NAME 
//				                     2) Change option setting of "LVS REDUCE SPLIT GATES" : default value is changed from "YES" to "NO" 
//				                     3) crtmom is using cell blocking 
//				                     4) Revise crtmom's logic operations. 
//				                     5) Revise metal interconnect logic operation : not exclude MOMDMY 
//				                     6) Revise Nwell resistors' logic operations. 
//				                     7) Revise 2T/3T mimcaps' logic operations and use ctm layer for mimcap's PLUS pin. 
//				                     8) Revise mimcap, R[PR] and R[NR] formations 
//				                     9) Metal datatypes are not limited to 0.  
//				                     10) Support bb 3T mimcap's bulk terminal in NWELL. 
//				                     11) Add a switch "OD_RES_WO_DMNP2V" : Default is off.  
//				                         This switch is for 2T/3T non-silicide OD resistor. 
//				                         2T/3T non-silicide P+/N+ OD resistors should w/i DMP2V if it's turn off. 
//				                     12) mnpg and mpgg of ERC check include all mos, but exclude rf mos.  
//				                     13) Base band mos in RFDUMMY1 could be extracted in netlist. 
//				                     14) Use wpe search distance layer "OD2" for I/O pmos. 
// 
// 09/30/2011    1.2a_pre093011  L.Fu  	 1) Update follow T-018-CM-SP-007 v1.2
//                                       2) Add LVS deck to support metalscheme 1P3M
// 01/28/2013    1.2a            X.M.Tu  Official release 
//                                       1) Just promote version to v1.2a                                          
// 11/28/2016    1.3a            X.M.Tu  Official release 
//                                       1) Just promote version to v1.3a
 

